title._content: Barstow, Zedekiah and Elizabeth of Keene NH

description._content: TITLE Barstow, Zedekiah and Elizabeth of Keene NH CREATOR French, J.A., and Daniel Sawyer, Keene NH SUBJECT People - NH - Keene Clergy - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Stereograph of Zedekiah Smith Barstow and Elizabeth Fay Blake Barstow of Keene New Hampshire. Zedekiah was born in 1790 in Canterbury CT and died in Keene in 1873. Elizabeth was born in 1792 in Westboro MA and died in Keene in 1869. Dr. Barstow graduated from Yale and Dartmouth and was ordained in 1818. He started the Cheshire Theological Institute and was the last minister settled by the town before the separation of civil and church authority. He officiated until he was 80 years old. Elizabeth was the niece of Eli Whitney the inventor.
